WEBVTT

00:16.016 --> 00:17.147
[KNIFE SWISHING]

00:31.857 --> 00:33.163
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

00:39.256 --> 00:41.041
[OFFICER
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

00:41.084 --> 00:43.869
[GROANS]
What the hell
happened here?

00:43.913 --> 00:45.915
We got ambushed
a few minutes ago.

00:45.958 --> 00:47.221
You okay?

00:47.264 --> 00:50.659
I hurt my arm when I got
thrown from the vehicle.

00:50.702 --> 00:53.140
Everyone else was
shot at close range.

00:53.183 --> 00:55.881
You're from
the other facility?Yeah.

00:55.925 --> 00:58.319
I was until Jericho
ordered us to bug out.

00:58.362 --> 01:01.452
OFFICER: Well, he just
flew in from another camp
and he's on a war path.

01:01.496 --> 01:03.628
So get your ass in the truck.
With the bus here now,

01:03.672 --> 01:05.369
Armstrong wants
all hands on deck.

01:05.413 --> 01:08.068
Armstrong?
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

01:08.111 --> 01:10.244
I said hustle up.

01:10.287 --> 01:12.159
We'll send out a crew
to take care of this mess.

01:12.202 --> 01:14.596
[MUFFLED HEARTBEATS]

02:04.211 --> 02:08.389
Flynn, someone
on the phone for you.

02:23.099 --> 02:25.667
Here, bud.

02:25.710 --> 02:28.409
Hello.
NICK: Flynn? It's me, Dad.

02:28.452 --> 02:32.674
Oh, uh... Oh, my God.
Dad, are you okay?

02:37.722 --> 02:42.553
Yeah, I'm fine, buddy.
I'm fine, buddy.
Your mom's with me, too.

02:42.597 --> 02:43.946
Uh...

02:45.208 --> 02:46.514
Are you safe?
Yeah. Uh...

02:46.557 --> 02:48.603
Me and Grandpa
are at the old farmhouse.

02:48.646 --> 02:50.822
You guys having
a good time?

02:50.866 --> 02:52.998
It's better than I expected.
Where are you?

02:53.042 --> 02:57.046
[STAMMERING] We're... We're...

02:57.089 --> 03:00.963
We're pretty far away.
But we're going
to be home soon.

03:01.006 --> 03:02.617
How soon?
Soon.

03:06.229 --> 03:09.058
Your mother and I
just have to

03:09.101 --> 03:11.278
take care of one more thing
before we leave.

03:15.412 --> 03:16.718
Flynn...

03:18.807 --> 03:20.330
I love you, you hear me?

03:20.374 --> 03:22.985
I do, Dad, I love you too.

03:23.028 --> 03:25.683
I'll see you soon, okay?
I can't wait.

03:25.727 --> 03:27.772
All right, bye.
Bye.

03:35.171 --> 03:38.392
The organ harvesting,
the files,
the other prisoners,

03:38.435 --> 03:39.610
it's all connected.

03:42.134 --> 03:44.528
We got to go up
and over the hill.

03:53.581 --> 03:55.278
[KIDS CHATTERING
IN DISTANCE]

04:08.683 --> 04:10.119
Hey, it's okay. It's okay.

04:12.730 --> 04:15.646
It's okay. She's...

04:16.168 --> 04:17.996
She's...

04:18.040 --> 04:20.085
She's my family,
I... I trust her.

04:22.262 --> 04:25.047
[SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE]

04:25.700 --> 04:27.267
This is Emily.

04:27.310 --> 04:32.794
This is Rafiq,
Imat, Amira, Ali

04:32.837 --> 04:34.317
and Yara.

04:35.884 --> 04:36.885
Hi.

04:38.147 --> 04:41.063
Their parents
are in a refugee
prison camp.

04:45.285 --> 04:47.156
That's the one
I was telling you about.

04:49.854 --> 04:51.334
I promised I'd help them.

04:55.991 --> 04:57.122
[STUTTERS]

05:09.483 --> 05:13.617
[SNIFFS] I promised Flynn
that I would bring you home.

05:16.620 --> 05:19.536
I know, but if it was Flynn,
if it was Flynn out here,

05:20.842 --> 05:22.800
I hope someone would
do the same for him.

06:48.190 --> 06:50.975
Off the top of your head,
any suspects come to mind?

06:54.196 --> 06:55.806
Who isn't one at this point?

06:57.765 --> 07:01.116
I got 40-odd agents and staff
I got to look at
all over again.

07:04.336 --> 07:07.209
But first, I got to break
the news to the department.

07:13.345 --> 07:15.870
Deputy Director Webb
has offered to do it.

07:15.913 --> 07:18.786
He barely even knew Thompson,
probably never even
spoke to her.

07:20.178 --> 07:21.832
I can do it.

07:21.876 --> 07:23.921
Unless you...
[SIGHS] No...

07:23.965 --> 07:27.098
I put her on the case,
I'll do it.

07:27.882 --> 07:28.970
I'll do it.

07:31.799 --> 07:32.887
[GROANS]

07:41.417 --> 07:44.812
RAFIQ: Every day
they take a group of people
and move them to cages behind.

07:44.855 --> 07:46.944
[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY
IN DISTANCE]

07:46.988 --> 07:50.513
Ali's dad went yesterday,
his uncle is still
in the main part.

07:53.473 --> 07:56.954
A lot of guns
for a refugee camp.

07:56.998 --> 08:00.305
So, what is Meridian
doing with them?RAFIQ: That's the boss!

08:05.528 --> 08:07.661
I'm, uh, Elliot,
I work here.

08:07.704 --> 08:10.881
EMILY: I know him.
I talked to him in Berlin.

08:27.202 --> 08:29.552
All right,
let's get out of here
before anybody sees us.

08:29.596 --> 08:30.553
Everybody stay low.

08:33.121 --> 08:34.557
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

09:06.763 --> 09:08.460
[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

09:43.583 --> 09:45.019
[ALL CLAMORING]

10:11.001 --> 10:13.482
What did she say to you?
Nothing.

10:17.747 --> 10:20.184
They held me at gunpoint
as they spoke with you.

10:22.665 --> 10:23.927
Really?

10:28.366 --> 10:29.716
Emily Byrne
is the reason

10:29.759 --> 10:32.327
we're shutting down
our Austrian facilities.

10:32.370 --> 10:33.850
I didn't have a choice.

10:35.460 --> 10:37.332
We always have a choice.

10:39.551 --> 10:43.294
Perhaps you should ask Berlin
for further instructions.

10:54.436 --> 10:55.872
I don't answer to them.

10:59.136 --> 11:00.616
You wanted
to see me, sir?

11:04.272 --> 11:07.449
I'd like to say
I'm sorry for this.

11:12.019 --> 11:13.411
[SNIFFS] But that
would be a lie.

11:29.253 --> 11:30.733
[SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE]

11:31.691 --> 11:33.693
[STUTTERING] Uh, Rafiq...

11:33.736 --> 11:35.912
She wants to know
if you play soccer.

11:35.956 --> 11:40.047
Oh, uh... No, I'm more of
a baseball, hockey guy.

11:40.090 --> 11:41.744
Will you translate?

11:42.440 --> 11:44.138
Baseball... Hockey...

11:47.271 --> 11:49.752
So, what about you?
I play poker.

11:50.710 --> 11:51.841
Yeah?
RAFIQ: Mmm.

11:51.885 --> 11:54.496
NICK: Texas hold'em?
Yeah.

11:56.324 --> 11:58.456
Nick... [STAMMERING]
Hold the kids back.

12:01.546 --> 12:03.418
I'll be right back. Okay?

12:08.379 --> 12:09.685
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

12:26.093 --> 12:27.224
Move your ass.

12:31.185 --> 12:32.882
Come on, go! Go!

12:37.365 --> 12:39.497
Get that nurse
out of here.

13:06.960 --> 13:09.136
I want another man
on that tower by nightfall.

13:09.179 --> 13:10.354
Do you hear me?

13:29.112 --> 13:30.070
[GROANS]

13:35.162 --> 13:36.250
[BOTH GRUNTING]

13:45.476 --> 13:46.477
[STRAINING]

13:50.003 --> 13:51.395
[GASPING]

14:03.190 --> 14:05.453
How come we haven't been here
since I was little?

14:07.324 --> 14:10.501
Came here
a lot before your
grandma died.

14:12.025 --> 14:13.417
A lot of memories.

14:14.375 --> 14:16.420
This farm was a little refuge.

14:20.250 --> 14:21.512
My mom once told me

14:21.556 --> 14:23.863
you taught her
how to survive
in the world.

14:23.906 --> 14:25.647
Sure. A few things
here and there.

14:27.127 --> 14:29.564
Did you learn that
in the army?

14:29.607 --> 14:32.045
Little in basic training,
most I learned in combat.

14:33.089 --> 14:34.264
What was it like?

14:36.179 --> 14:39.922
I was afraid. We all were.

14:39.966 --> 14:42.403
Did you hate it?
You bet.

14:42.446 --> 14:45.319
I still got the nightmares
to prove it.

14:45.362 --> 14:49.366
But also...
Also I never
felt so alive.

14:49.410 --> 14:50.802
I never understood that.

14:51.847 --> 14:55.416
You feel this
cold sweat of fear,

14:55.459 --> 14:58.462
your hands are trembling,
your entire body shaking...

15:04.686 --> 15:06.166
On this one,

15:07.254 --> 15:10.518
take a breath, in, out,

15:10.561 --> 15:12.476
long, slow,

15:12.520 --> 15:14.783
pause

15:14.826 --> 15:16.306
and then release.

15:20.006 --> 15:21.050
[EXHALES]

15:27.317 --> 15:28.579
It worked.
You see?

15:34.020 --> 15:36.109
Hey! Careful.

15:36.152 --> 15:37.806
Right in front of you. See?

15:37.849 --> 15:39.590
That's our old well.

15:39.634 --> 15:41.418
You don't want
to fall down there.

15:42.854 --> 15:43.899
[GRUNTS]

15:43.943 --> 15:45.553
Grandpa, are you okay?

15:45.596 --> 15:48.251
Yeah, yeah.
I'm just a bit tired.

15:49.905 --> 15:52.125
Do you mind
getting me some water?Sure.

15:52.168 --> 15:53.387
[SIGHS]

15:55.476 --> 15:56.825
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

16:22.024 --> 16:25.419
Hello?
Uncle Jack,
it's me, Flynn.

16:25.462 --> 16:28.465
Flynn, hey. How's the farm?
Yeah.

16:28.509 --> 16:31.686
It's good. Mom and Dad called. They're coming home soon.

16:31.729 --> 16:34.558
Yeah, yeah. I know.
It's great news.

16:34.602 --> 16:36.734
But there's something else.

16:36.778 --> 16:39.302
Yeah? What is it?
I'm worried about Grandpa.

16:40.825 --> 16:42.392
Why? Has something happened?

16:42.436 --> 16:45.613
We've been doing
a lot of outdoor stuff
so maybe he's just...

16:45.656 --> 16:47.136
Has he been taking
his heart medication?

16:47.180 --> 16:49.051
Yeah, he...
He took it last night.

16:49.095 --> 16:52.141
Okay, good.
Well, he's supposed
to take two every day.

16:52.185 --> 16:53.925
Of course, if you ask him
if he's been taking it,

16:53.969 --> 16:56.928
he'll just bark at you
and tell you to mind
your own damn business.

16:56.972 --> 16:59.148
He also likes
to chop a lot of wood
while he's up there.

16:59.192 --> 17:00.976
Don't let him
do too much, okay?

17:01.020 --> 17:03.500
Okay, I'll let you know
if anything happens
to Grandpa.

17:03.544 --> 17:05.154
Okay, sounds good.

17:05.981 --> 17:07.287
I'll talk to you later.

17:07.330 --> 17:08.766
All right, bye.

17:19.212 --> 17:22.389
That was a fresh massacre
that we saw out there.

17:22.432 --> 17:25.696
We need to find out
when exactly the FBI
is getting here.

17:33.269 --> 17:37.447
If you could call
one person at the FBI,

17:37.491 --> 17:40.059
to let them know
what's happening out here,

17:40.102 --> 17:41.756
who would it be?

17:44.672 --> 17:48.545
Gifty Thompson was new here,
but already she was one of us.

17:49.938 --> 17:53.072
A member of the family,
a member of the tribe.

17:54.638 --> 17:58.860
She was a driven agent.

17:58.903 --> 18:03.995
Diligent with... [CHUCKLES]
With a unique sense of humor.

18:04.039 --> 18:07.260
And most importantly,
she was always...Special Agent Crown...

18:07.303 --> 18:10.306
I'm sorry to interrupt,
but there's an urgent
phone call for you.

18:10.350 --> 18:11.655
Sharon, you can see
I'm busy here.

18:11.699 --> 18:13.657
You're gonna want to
take this right now.

18:15.311 --> 18:17.661
If there's a problem,
I'm happy to take over.

18:17.705 --> 18:21.535
It's okay,
Deputy Director.
I can continue.

18:21.578 --> 18:23.580
All right, I'll take it
in the conference room.

18:25.539 --> 18:26.583
[CLEARS THROAT]

18:29.282 --> 18:31.327
This is Special Agent Crown,
who am I speaking to?

18:31.371 --> 18:33.764
NICK: [CHUCKLING]
Derek, it's so good
to hear your voice.

18:33.808 --> 18:35.026
Nick!

18:35.070 --> 18:37.986
[STAMMERING]
How are you? Where are you?

18:39.944 --> 18:41.903
Wait... Didn't...

18:41.946 --> 18:43.948
Didn't Thompson give you
my message yesterday?

18:43.992 --> 18:46.647
Oh, man, Thompson's dead.

18:51.347 --> 18:55.873
Derek, I... I spoke with her.
I told her that I escaped.

18:55.917 --> 18:57.919
[STUTTERING] Listen, Derek,

18:57.962 --> 18:59.660
Meridian has
a group of refugees

18:59.703 --> 19:03.098
locked up
in some kind of
prison compound.

19:03.142 --> 19:05.100
They're going
to kill them.What?

19:05.144 --> 19:08.669
I need you to get
an Interpol extraction team
out here, ASAP.

19:08.712 --> 19:12.194
Okay, listen, I'm going
to send the fucking cavalry
in to get you.

19:12.238 --> 19:14.805
Tell me exactly where you are.

19:14.849 --> 19:16.155
Where?

19:16.198 --> 19:18.679
Just outside of Schonbrunn
on the Austrian border.

19:18.722 --> 19:21.856
But we need to get
a team on the ground
over there to get him out.

19:21.899 --> 19:22.987
I've already
put that in motion

19:23.031 --> 19:24.772
with the State Department
and Interpol.

19:24.815 --> 19:26.165
Good.

19:26.730 --> 19:27.905
[SIGHS]

19:28.993 --> 19:30.081
Thank God.

19:31.213 --> 19:32.388
Nick's alive.

19:34.216 --> 19:37.045
Did he mention anything
about Special Agent Isaac?

19:37.088 --> 19:39.265
Nothing.

19:39.308 --> 19:41.484
Okay, I better
check in with State,
see where they're at.

19:41.528 --> 19:42.920
Good idea.

20:05.204 --> 20:07.075
I'm shutting down
the compound now.

20:07.118 --> 20:09.643
Will erase all traces
of what we were doing here.

20:09.686 --> 20:11.862
Yes, of course.

20:11.906 --> 20:14.648
I'm getting them ready
as we speak. They'll
be with you shortly.

20:15.823 --> 20:17.259
Thank you.

20:34.668 --> 20:36.017
Best case,

20:36.060 --> 20:38.498
an extraction team
is at least 12 hours out.

20:40.369 --> 20:42.545
That's going to take too long.

20:42.589 --> 20:44.721
It's up to us
to do something.

20:49.813 --> 20:51.989
We need to create a diversion
to get us inside.

20:53.991 --> 20:55.776
The kids know
the guards' schedule.

20:55.819 --> 20:58.822
Maybe they also know
a way on the other side
of that fence.

20:58.866 --> 21:01.869
We got to get to Elliot.

21:01.912 --> 21:04.698
We do. And then we force
his guards to stand down.

21:04.741 --> 21:07.483
Cut the head off the snake?
Mmm-hmm.

21:07.527 --> 21:09.398
We got to move soon.

21:09.442 --> 21:11.879
If we wait any longer,
their families will be dead.

21:11.922 --> 21:13.837
[GUN LOADING]
Here.

21:42.301 --> 21:44.346
Flynn! Get in here.

21:44.390 --> 21:47.393
What?
Get in here.

21:57.359 --> 21:59.143
Get inside.

22:16.596 --> 22:17.858
You make
a hell of an entrance.

22:17.901 --> 22:19.729
[LAUGHS] Hey, Pop.

22:19.773 --> 22:21.818
Hey, bud, how you doing?

22:21.862 --> 22:23.951
Good.
Great to see you.

22:23.994 --> 22:25.431
Yeah. You, too.

22:25.474 --> 22:27.171
I decided to take
a couple of days off.

22:27.215 --> 22:30.740
Great.
Hey Flynn!
How are you?

22:30.784 --> 22:32.089
Did I miss all the fun?

22:32.133 --> 22:34.353
I learned
how to shoot a bow.Yeah?

22:39.967 --> 22:42.752
Were you followed?
What? No. I don't think so.

22:42.796 --> 22:44.406
WARREN: Come on.
Let's get inside.

23:04.339 --> 23:05.775
What the...

23:18.397 --> 23:20.224
I got something
you need to see.

23:20.268 --> 23:23.576
I correlated a list of who was
in the building when Nick
spoke to Thompson

23:23.619 --> 23:25.447
with another list
of who was in the building

23:25.491 --> 23:28.058
when Nick and Emily's
confidential FBI files
were leaked

23:28.102 --> 23:29.190
to Dawkins and Meridian.

23:29.233 --> 23:33.150
And?
One name. Both lists.

23:38.155 --> 23:39.418
Oh, my God.

23:40.593 --> 23:41.811
Deputy Director Webb.

23:43.857 --> 23:45.249
Facts don't lie, Julianne.

23:45.293 --> 23:46.860
[JULIANNE SIGHS]

23:46.903 --> 23:50.690
Webb can't be the informant.
He has too much at stake.

23:50.733 --> 23:52.300
This is where
the evidence leads.

23:55.216 --> 23:57.914
He's been my mentor
since my first
field assignment.

23:57.958 --> 24:00.003
Yeah, I know.

24:06.706 --> 24:09.535
We need to be 100% about this.
You know that, right?

24:09.578 --> 24:10.971
I do.

24:13.016 --> 24:16.019
Webb's politically connected.
We can't get this wrong.

24:16.063 --> 24:19.066
We can't make an accusation
that we can't back up
with evidence.

24:19.109 --> 24:21.372
All right,
so we make this airtight.

24:21.416 --> 24:22.678
We need more.

24:22.722 --> 24:24.506
Why can't we just
bring him in for questioning?

24:24.550 --> 24:27.074
No, not yet. We need more
than you have in this folder.

24:27.117 --> 24:29.511
[SCOFFS] Look, come on,
this is bullshit.

24:29.555 --> 24:31.165
He's guilty.

24:31.208 --> 24:33.254
I know
you want to move fast,

24:33.297 --> 24:34.951
but we need
something concrete

24:34.995 --> 24:36.344
if we're gonna
make this stick.

24:39.216 --> 24:40.479
[SIGHS]

24:53.883 --> 24:57.060
ELLIOT: Emily, I've been
fucking helping you
this entire time!

24:57.104 --> 24:59.802
EMILY: I don't have
the time to figure out
if I can trust you.

25:00.716 --> 25:02.501
Will you pass me a little?

25:02.544 --> 25:03.893
NICK: Thank you.
Thank you.

25:10.509 --> 25:12.293
You and Nick have a son?

25:13.033 --> 25:14.904
Yeah, we do.

25:16.079 --> 25:19.082
What's his name?
His name's Flynn.

25:19.648 --> 25:20.780
Ah.

25:23.043 --> 25:26.220
What does he want to be
when he grows up?

25:26.263 --> 25:28.657
I don't know
that he's figured
that out just yet.

25:28.701 --> 25:30.398
I want to be a doctor.

25:30.441 --> 25:32.792
Yeah?
Mmm.

25:32.835 --> 25:34.924
My brother's
a doctor, you know.My father was, too.

25:34.968 --> 25:39.102
He worked
in a hospital in Homs.Thanks.

25:39.146 --> 25:42.758
His specialty was
children's eye surgery.

25:45.500 --> 25:46.719
Beautiful.

25:49.286 --> 25:50.549
Where's your dad now?

25:55.641 --> 25:56.772
He died.

25:57.643 --> 25:58.731
Last year in the war.

25:59.819 --> 26:01.037
Only have my mother now.

26:03.300 --> 26:04.345
I'm sorry.

26:08.828 --> 26:11.744
Will you and Nick

26:11.787 --> 26:13.572
really try and rescue
our families?

26:15.965 --> 26:17.227
Yeah.

26:20.491 --> 26:22.058
Thank you
for helping us, Emily.

26:24.495 --> 26:25.671
[NICK TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

26:28.978 --> 26:30.719
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

26:42.862 --> 26:44.515
[ALL TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

26:57.746 --> 26:59.226
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

27:00.183 --> 27:02.142
[WHISTLING IN DISTANCE]

27:02.185 --> 27:03.709
Everyone is ready.
It's time.

27:08.322 --> 27:12.631
Okay, when we're done...
When we're done,
you two stay here.

27:12.674 --> 27:14.676
Stay here this time,
where it's safe.

27:14.720 --> 27:17.070
Okay? I'm...
I'm serious.

27:17.113 --> 27:20.029
[STUTTERING]
There's the cameras.

27:20.073 --> 27:21.204
Stick to the right side
of the fence.

27:21.248 --> 27:22.423
NICK: All right.

27:24.425 --> 27:25.687
Ready?

27:26.557 --> 27:28.342
RAFIQ: Clear?
Clear.

27:43.574 --> 27:45.141
Get Armstrong. Now.

28:18.871 --> 28:22.657
So, we have
an unexpected guest.

28:22.701 --> 28:24.006
Find who did this.

28:32.711 --> 28:34.147
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

28:52.992 --> 28:54.471
[WHISTLING IN DISTANCE]

29:00.390 --> 29:01.957
Report. Upper levels?
All's clear.

29:02.001 --> 29:04.307
Lower levels.
Still working on it.

29:04.351 --> 29:05.831
ARMSTRONG: We need to
find this intruder.

29:05.874 --> 29:07.441
Get a move on it.

29:16.450 --> 29:17.973
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

29:21.934 --> 29:23.979
Ready? Now.

29:28.288 --> 29:29.593
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

29:35.774 --> 29:38.689
Come on, we're on
a time scale. Move it.

29:38.733 --> 29:41.518
They want this place
shut down ASAP.

29:41.562 --> 29:42.868
[WHISTLING IN DISTANCE]
[EXPLOSION]

29:45.261 --> 29:46.697
[MEN CLAMORING]

29:53.617 --> 29:55.619
[INDISTINCT
ANNOUNCEMENT OVER PA]

30:06.152 --> 30:07.980
Sir?

30:08.023 --> 30:11.374
What is it?
We're being attacked.

30:11.418 --> 30:13.724
Someone is trying
to storm our compound.

30:13.768 --> 30:15.814
ELLIOT: This is happening
faster than I expected.

30:17.467 --> 30:18.817
[WHISTLING IN DISTANCE]

30:26.563 --> 30:28.043
[CLAMORING]

30:32.091 --> 30:33.788
[ALARM BLARING]

30:37.009 --> 30:38.793
Go.

30:46.975 --> 30:48.455
Speed up the shutdown.

30:48.498 --> 30:50.979
Inject the refugees.
The ones in the pen?

30:51.023 --> 30:52.546
No. All of them.

30:52.589 --> 30:54.548
We need to make it look like
the virus swept through here.

30:54.591 --> 30:57.420
These injections need time
to take effect.

30:58.639 --> 31:01.598
So up the concentration
so they die faster.

31:02.251 --> 31:04.340
Go!

31:04.384 --> 31:06.299
[ALARM BLARING IN DISTANCE]

31:34.936 --> 31:36.720
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

31:39.985 --> 31:41.856
Really?
Yeah.

31:41.900 --> 31:44.641
I used to catch
a dozen shellfish a day
down in that lake.

31:46.208 --> 31:48.907
Did you eat them?
No.

31:48.950 --> 31:51.474
Threw 'em back
so I could catch 'em again.

31:53.650 --> 31:55.478
Hey, where's Grandpa?

31:55.522 --> 31:57.959
I thought he was closing up
the barn for the night.

31:58.003 --> 32:00.266
Yeah, me, too.
He should be done by now.

32:03.182 --> 32:05.924
Dad! You in the barn?

32:10.145 --> 32:11.190
Dad?

32:12.626 --> 32:14.236
Can you hear me?
Say something!

32:34.691 --> 32:37.042
Listen, Flynn, I need you
to do something for me.

32:37.085 --> 32:38.521
It's probably nothing.

32:40.001 --> 32:41.916
I need you to hide
in this closet

32:41.960 --> 32:43.265
and don't come out
until I tell you it's okay.

32:43.309 --> 32:44.527
All right.
Okay.

32:52.709 --> 32:54.102
Dad?

33:01.892 --> 33:03.242
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

33:06.332 --> 33:08.334
MAN: We need you
on the second floor.

33:10.858 --> 33:12.512
[ALARM BLARING IN DISTANCE]

33:19.519 --> 33:21.086
[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

33:49.157 --> 33:51.855
MAN: Move it!
Move it! Keep moving!

34:03.954 --> 34:05.217
[PANTING]

34:06.218 --> 34:08.089
[BOTH GRUNTING]

34:15.792 --> 34:17.142
Dad?

34:19.796 --> 34:21.189
[FOOTSTEPS]

34:37.684 --> 34:38.902
[DOOR OPENS]
[DISTANT GROANING]

34:55.223 --> 34:56.485
[GROANING]

35:01.316 --> 35:04.885
You take one more step
and the old man dies.

35:04.928 --> 35:06.756
Take the shot, Jack.

35:06.800 --> 35:08.106
[SHUSHES]

35:11.848 --> 35:13.589
Now set the gun down.

35:13.633 --> 35:15.113
On the table.

35:19.726 --> 35:21.467
I won't ask you again.

35:37.918 --> 35:39.398
Good man.

35:47.057 --> 35:48.798
Now, where's the boy?

35:48.842 --> 35:50.278
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

35:52.411 --> 35:53.368
[WARREN GROANING]

35:54.500 --> 35:55.718
[GRUNTING]

35:58.243 --> 36:00.201
That was silly,
wasn't it, Papa?

36:00.245 --> 36:01.202
[CHUCKLES]

36:18.306 --> 36:19.264
[CHUCKLES]

36:29.143 --> 36:30.492
ELLIOT: Destroy
the patient files

36:30.536 --> 36:32.277
and the clinical
trial results.

36:32.320 --> 36:35.193
ASSISTANT:
Even the lab reports?Yes.

36:36.498 --> 36:37.847
[SHREDDER WHIRRING]

36:41.677 --> 36:43.897
I want nothing
of value left behind.

36:58.520 --> 37:00.130
I was wondering
when we'd meet again.

37:00.174 --> 37:02.002
Tell your guards
to stand down.

37:02.742 --> 37:04.222
Get on the radio, now.

37:17.322 --> 37:18.279
[GUARD GRUNTS]

37:19.193 --> 37:21.195
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
